<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Prompt templates control the structured fields sent to the LLM for each event shape.
  `source` values are stable internal tokens; `label` is the model-facing field name.
  System prompts and final instructions may be overridden here. When blank, DiaryPromptDef.xml
  supplies the shared default text.
  Event-specific prompt guidance comes from two XML layers:
    - DiaryEventPromptDef.prompt/enhancement -> "event prompt" and "event enhancement"
    - DiaryInteractionGroupDef.instruction -> narrower group flavor

  Writing-style note: the pawn's style is NOT a field here anymore. It is appended to the system
  prompt at dispatch (DiaryPromptPlanner.Build via PromptAssembler.ComposeSystem) so the style governs
  HOW the entry is written. First-person shapes keep the default includePersona=true; the neutral
  death/arrival chronicles and the title flow set includePersona=false to stay style-free.
  (A custom template can still add <li><source>Persona</source></li> to put the style back into the
  user message if you prefer that. The source token remains Persona for compatibility.)
-->
